Q2 — Write double(x)
Make double(x) return 2 * x. Keep the function name the same.
Grading is behavior-based, so x*2 and 2*x both pass (and it must work on vectors).












Return 2 * x (or x * 2 — both are fine).




double &lt;- function(x) {
  2 * x
}
double(5)
double &lt;- function(x) {
  2 * x
}
double(5)
